Abdomen
: Male terminalia small compared to other abdominal segments, in ventral view width 0.5X VIII segment width (
Fig. 8A
). Genitalia. Lateral plate with postero-dorsal finger-like process (
Fig. 8C
). Subgenital plate narrow, length 2.5X width, fused until half-length (
Fig. 8B
); lobes with long setae throughout (setae longer than lobes width) (
Fig. 8
B–C). Style in ventral view stout throughout, apex finger shaped, directed laterally (
Fig. 8B
); in lateral view broader at middle, apex rounded and more or less hook-shaped (
Fig. 8C
). Aedeagus in lateral view Ushaped (
Fig. 8C
), posterior arm wider at apical third, tapering apically, with denticles on anterior face of apical third (
Fig. 8
C–D); gonopore ovoid, located on apical third of posterior arm (
Fig. 8
C–D).

Biology.
One teneral was found on a plant of the genus 

Solanum

L. (
Solanaceae
) in a small patch of cloud forest (
Fig. 7F
). The exuviae were found under a leaf near to the branch apex (
Fig. 7E
). Although, several explorations in the area were made, just one specimen was collected.
